== Procedure == #Season ribs with Rub. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. #Place applewood in the firebox of a 250 smoker '''''or''''' the coal area of a 250 charcoal grill set for indirect heat. #Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil over high heat until reduced by 1/3. Cover tightly and set aside. #Place ribs in smoker/on top of grill grate and cook, brushing often with preserve mixture, for 5-6 hours. #Brush ribs generously with preserve mixture and place on a medium high grill and cook, repeatedly brushing side facing you, until well browned. Repeat one more time. #Remove and let rest 10 minutes; slice into 1-rib portions and serve.

{{stages}}

This worksheet will help practice with order of operations. As a reminder, the following rules apply:
# Do the equations in parentheses/brackets first. If the question has nested brackets like [] and {}, do the equations in inner bracket first. Inner equations symbolized as ().
# Do multiplication and division before addition and subtraction.
# Do the equation in order from left to right.

There are two worksheets, based on whole numbers or fractions:
