{{Wikipedia|Bootstrapping (statistics)}}
<noinclude>{{R Programming/Navigation}}</noinclude>
{{...}}
* '''boot''' package includes functions from the book ''Bootstrap Methods and Their Applications'' by A. C. Davison and D. V. Hinkley (1997, CUP) * '''bootstrap''' package.
== Quick how-to ==
Do a boostrap of some data for some function (here, mean): b <- boot(data, function(data, id) { mean(data[id]) }, 1000) Use this to compute a 90%-confidence interval: boot.ci(b, .9, type="norm")
== References ==
{{reflist}}
* Instructions for the '''boot''' package: http://www.statmethods.net/advstats/bootstrapping.html * Sample using the '''boot''' package: http://druedin.com/2012/11/10/bootstrapping-in-r/
